 {"id":"bd-17ed","title":"Input Macro Recording and Playback","description":"# Input Macro Recording and Playback

## Background & Motivation

Testing interactive flows requires either:
- Manual testing (slow, non-reproducible)
- Hardcoded input sequences (brittle, hard to maintain)

**The solution:**
- Record input events as deterministic macros
- Replay them for automated testing
- Export for documentation and demos

**Relationship to existing beads:**
- Extends bd-10i.8.3 (ProgramSimulator) with input recording
- Enhances bd-2ky9 (E2E tests) with reproducible inputs

## Technical Design

```rust
pub struct InputMacro {
    events: Vec<TimedEvent>,
    name: String,
    metadata: MacroMetadata,
}

pub struct TimedEvent {
    event: Event,
    delay_ms: u32,
}

pub struct MacroMetadata {
    recorded_at: DateTime<Utc>,
    terminal_size: (u16, u16),
    app_version: String,
}

impl InputMacro {
    pub fn record(events: impl Iterator<Item = Event>) -> Self { ... }
    pub fn replay(&self, sender: &EventSender) { ... }
    pub fn save(&self, path: &Path) -> io::Result<()> { ... }
    pub fn load(path: &Path) -> io::Result<Self> { ... }
}
```

## Logging Requirements

```rust
// Recording start (INFO level)
tracing::info!(macro_name = name, "Starting input recording");

// Event recorded (DEBUG level)
tracing::debug!(event = ?event, delay_ms = delay, "Event recorded");

// Playback start (INFO level)
tracing::info!(macro_name = name, event_count = events.len(), "Starting macro playback");

// Playback event (TRACE level)
tracing::trace!(event = ?event, index = i, "Replaying event");
```

## E2E Tests

```bash
# Record a form submission macro
./ftui-harness --record-macro form_submit.yaml --scenario form

# Replay and validate
./ftui-harness --replay-macro form_submit.yaml --assert-final-state expected.json

# Verify determinism
./scripts/macro-determinism-test.sh form_submit.yaml --runs 10
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Recording captures all input events accurately
- [ ] Playback is deterministic (same output every run)
- [ ] Timing preserved for realistic replay
- [ ] File format is human-readable (YAML)
- [ ] Metadata includes terminal size and app version
- [ ] Integration with test framework via ProgramSimulator
- [ ] All tests pass","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-01T03:11:09.913883724Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-01T19:44:03.679226782Z","closed_at":"2026-02-01T19:44:03.679205903Z","close_reason":"Implemented InputMacro, TimedEvent, MacroMetadata types, MacroRecorder, MacroPlayer with step/replay_all/replay_until/reset. 18 tests covering recording, playback, timing, quit handling, determinism, reset, mixed events.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-17ed","depends_on_id":"bd-10i.8.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T16:31:30Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-17h9","title":"Demo Showcase: UI Inspector + Hit-Test Overlay","description":"Interactive inspector showing widget tree, bounds, and hit-test regions with hover highlighting.

## Success Criteria
- Epic delivers a cohesive user-visible capability: Demo Showcase: UI Inspector + Hit-Test Overlay
- Child tasks are not just implemented; each has unit tests + E2E scripts with verbose JSONL logs and deterministic fixtures
- Graceful degradation tiers are specified (capabilities, fallbacks, safety) and validated in tests


## Alien Artifact Upgrades
- Model the core decision(s) with explicit state, priors/assumptions, and invariants; write down failure modes as first-class artifacts.
- Explainability: add an evidence ledger for any non-trivial decision (why this branch, why this fallback). Prefer Bayes factors / log-likelihood contributions over ad-hoc scoring.
- Guarantees: where prediction/thresholding exists, prefer distribution-free calibration (conformal prediction) or anytime-valid testing (e-process) so we can stop early without invalid inference.
- Graceful degradation: define capability tiers + deterministic fallbacks; never fail closed without a traceable reason.


## Extreme Optimization
- Baseline first: capture p50/p95/p99 for relevant command(s) with `hyperfine` (store raw output).
- Profile next: CPU flamegraph + allocation profile; identify top-5 hotspots.
- Opportunity matrix: implement only Score ≥ 2.0 (Impact×Confidence/Effort).
- Isomorphism proof per change: ordering, tie-breaking, RNG seeds, and golden checksums must match.
- Regression gates: add microbench + budgets; failures must print actionable deltas and include log artifacts.


## Testing Plan
- Unit tests: happy path + edge cases + regression fixtures.
- Property tests: invariants (idempotence, monotonicity, determinism) where applicable.
- Fuzz tests: parsers/state machines and any input-facing logic.
- Determinism: fixed seeds/time-freeze; snapshot fixtures must be stable.
